<https://www.reddit.com/r/3Dprinting/comments/gjksz2/ender_3_issue_z_axis_falling_down_tried_to/> > if steppers are disabled when the motor is off, it makes sense that it can move; once you move the z axis when the machine is on, the stepper is enabled. Something like [this](https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08LZ1V56T?_encoding=UTF8&ref_=cm_sw_r_cp_ud_dp_G7DTYEBJ17MBDZGAKB60&th=1) can also help

M500 | save EEPROM
M302         ; report current cold extrusion state
M302 P0      ; enable cold extrusion checking
M302 P1      ; disable cold extrusion checking
M302 S0      ; always allow extrusion (disable checking)
M302 S170    ; only allow extrusion above 170
M302 S170 P1 ; set min extrude temp to 170 but leave disabled


de belt is slipping on the gears of the stepper motor so the axis is not moving; after replacing the pulley with the correct teeth size it's slipping on the big printed one instead. I realized I tightened the assembly without a bearing at the top so the big one couldn't move. After stacking it again with a bearing and an angled washer it worked.

if im not locking the POM nut to the threaded rod, it's just gonna disconnect itself from the pusher when going up, so I made a custom locking nut but that didnt work so I butchered the print and added a custom nut on the bottom so it would be ok, however it also didn't work because the axis is just trying to destroy the rubber plunger instead, the resistance is too great.

now it's just that the Z axis falls down if the Z stepper is disabled after a set amount of seconds

## Gcode

Start: 

```
G90 ; use absolute coordinates
M83 ; extruder relative mode
M92 E1000 ; set E steps
M500; save EEPROM
M17 Z E; enable Z and E steppers immediately
M107 ; turn off fan
M302 S0 ; always allow extrusion (disable checking)
G28 ; home all axis
G1 Z5 F240
G1 X40 Y40 F3000
G1 Z3 F240 ; set first layer height as 3 mm
G92 E0
G1 Y140 E200 F1200 ; prime the nozzle
G1 X2.3 F5000
G92 E0
G1 Y10 E10 F1200 ; prime the nozzle
G92 E0
```

End:

```
{if max_layer_z < max_print_height}G1 Z{z_offset+min(max_layer_z+2, max_print_height)} F600 ; Move print head up{endif}
G1 X5 Y{print_bed_max[1]*0.8} F{travel_speed*60} ; present print
{if max_layer_z < max_print_height-10}G1 Z{z_offset+min(max_layer_z+70, max_print_height-10)} F600 ; Move print head further up{endif}
{if max_layer_z < max_print_height*0.6}G1 Z{max_print_height*0.6} F600 ; Move print head further up{endif}
M84 X Y E ; disable motors
```
